# Testing Rules

## Required test layers

- Rust unit tests for low-level correctness.
- Parity tests or vector-based tests for crypto logic when possible.
- JavaScript integration tests covering npm-facing APIs and WASM initialization behavior.

## Test priorities

- When changing crypto code, prioritize correctness tests first.
- When changing wrappers or exports, add or update JS integration tests.
- If a result is uncertain, do not guess; verify against the C++11 reference or known-good vectors.

## Scope

- Test both expected behavior and edge cases.
- Include tests for initialization, invalid inputs, and public API error handling.
- Prefer deterministic fixtures and reference vectors where possible.
